[div class=p 
	[a class=intlink href=/Users/Profile/feos 
		"feos
	]a
	": Accepting per the agreement about 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=out-of-bounds mouse movement in Flash|href=/Forum/Posts/521566)
	". It's too similar to simultaneous Left+Right which we 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=traditionally allow|href=/Forum/Topics/14051)
	", because it's just digital input that the platform accepts. While normally Flash games were (and still are) embedded into web sites, and the latter don't let you click the game outside the screen, it's on developers to properly handle things that official FlashPlayer can do.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"While sending OOB mouse input to FlashPlayer is currently not a thing to even test due to tools limitations, resizing its window to include the OOB area still makes it accessible for normal mouse input, and OOB input just simulates that.
	$LF
]div
